method_combination_logic.combination_strategy: Bayesian-causal fusion across 21 epistemologically heterogeneous methods. Causal structures are identified, then Bayesian posterior updating quantifies mechanism probabilities and intervention effects. Integration sequence: (1) Financial data extraction and quantitative baseline establishment; (2) Bayesian probabilistic analysis (5 methods) generates posterior distributions over hypotheses; (3) Structural validation and testing verify internal consistency and external benchmarks; (4) Bayesian-causal synthesis: posterior distributions over causal mechanisms inform final estimates with uncertainty quantification. Data transformations: Bayesian outputs (posterior distributions) → probability mass functions over hypotheses; Financial outputs (numerical assessments) → calibrated quantitative scores; Causal outputs (graphs, mechanisms) → validated causal pathway structures. This particularized strategy respects the intrinsic epistemological nature of each method class and ensures authentic intersection of heterogeneous evidence types into a coherent, structured answer for Q282 in PA10/DIM03.
method_combination_logic.rationale: D3-Q2 (Q012) for PA01/DIM03 requires consistent extraction, validation, and synthesis across 21 methods. This block documents how the pipeline combines method outputs into a single evidence product.
method_combination_logic.evidence_fusion: Evidence from all methods is aggregated by the EvidenceNexus according to evidence_assembly. Overlaps are deduplicated where possible and confidence is propagated conservatively.
method_combination_logic.confidence_aggregation: Confidence is aggregated via contract-defined merge strategies, favoring calibrated methods when available.
trade_offs: Coverage vs. cost: using 21 methods increases coverage but raises computation and maintenance burden.
Recall vs. precision: multiple detectors increase recall but can introduce redundancy; deduplication and weighting mitigate this.
Sophistication vs. interpretability: advanced models can be less transparent; human_readable_output documents assumptions and limitations.
